        <section class="doc-section" id="what-is-standard">
          <h2>What is Standard? <a href="#what-is-standard" class="doc-anchor">#</a></h2>
          <p>
            Standard is a comprehensive CSS framework that implements classical typography rules,
            mathematical precision with the golden ratio, and micro-typography principles inspired
            by the masters of print design.
          </p>

          <p>
            Built on research from Robert Bringhurst's "The Elements of Typographic Style," Ellen
            Lupton's typography works, and Swiss typography principles, Standard brings fine-art
            typography to the web.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="philosophy">
          <h2>Philosophy <a href="#philosophy" class="doc-anchor">#</a></h2>
          <p>Standard follows a simple principle:</p>

          <div class="doc-callout">
            <div class="doc-callout-title">💡 Core Principle</div>
            <p><strong>Respect classic typography rules, but readability always wins.</strong></p>
          </div>

          <p>The framework provides:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Zero-configuration setup with progressive enhancement</li>
            <li>Automatic multi-locale support</li>
            <li>Performance-optimized batch processing</li>
            <li>Modern web accessibility standards</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="features">
          <h2>Key Features <a href="#features" class="doc-anchor">#</a></h2>

          <h3>Mathematical Precision</h3>
          <p>
            Built on the golden ratio (φ = 1.618) and modular scale system for harmonious
            proportions:
          </p>

          <div class="doc-example">
            <div class="doc-example-title">CSS Variables</div>
            <pre><code>:root {
      --ratio-golden: 1.618;
      --ratio-silver: 1.414;
      --font-ratio: var(--ratio-silver);

      /* Modular scale */
      --scale-xs: calc(var(--font-size) * pow(var(--font-ratio), -1));
      --scale-s: calc(var(--font-size) * pow(var(--font-ratio), -0.5));
      --scale: var(--font-size);
      --scale-l: calc(var(--font-size) * pow(var(--font-ratio), 1));
      --scale-xl: calc(var(--font-size) * pow(var(--font-ratio), 2));
    }</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>Vertical Rhythm System</h3>
          <p>
            Bulletproof vertical rhythm using the <code>1rlh</code> (relative line height) unit:
          </p>

          <div class="doc-example">
            <div class="doc-example-title">HTML</div>
            <pre><code>&lt;html class="rhythm"&gt;
      &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;Perfect Spacing&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;All elements maintain consistent rhythm&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>Automatic Dark Mode</h3>
          <p>
            Respects system color scheme preferences with carefully crafted light and dark palettes:
          </p>

          <div class="doc-callout info">
            <div class="doc-callout-title">ℹ️ Automatic Detection</div>
            <p>
              Dark mode activates automatically based on <code>prefers-color-scheme</code> media
              query. No JavaScript required.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

